1. Nisam očekivao tvoj dolazak, *iznenađen sam.* (I am surprised. / Literally: I am surprised.)

2. Juče sam doživeo veliko *iznenađenje* kada sam dobio posao u inostranstvu. (Yesterday, I experienced a big surprise when I got a job abroad.)

3. Mala deca vole *iznenađenja* za rođendan. (Little kids love surprises for their birthday.)

4. Ne znam šta me čeka, pa sam pomalo *iznenađen.* (I don't know what awaits me, so I am a little surprised.)

5. On je spreman da organizuje mnogo *iznenađenja* za svoju devojku. (He is ready to organize a lot of surprises for his girlfriend.)

6. Čuo sam da je predsednik obećao veliko *iznenađenje* za građane. (I heard that the president promised a big surprise for the citizens.)

7. *Iznenađenje* koje sam doživeo kada sam video njeno lice je bilo neprocenjivo. (The surprise I experienced when I saw her face was priceless.)

8. Deca su se obradovala kada su videla veliko *iznenađenje* koje su im pripremili roditelji. (The children were delighted when they saw the big surprise their parents had prepared for them.)

9. Ona je znala da će joj prirediti *iznenađenje,* ali nije znala šta. (She knew he would surprise her, but she didn't know what.)

10. *Iznenađenja* u životu mogu biti i dobra i loša. (Surprises in life can be both good and bad.)